<keyLead id="30ABBA4D3E473C6C9EACFCB2F68DFCD2" box="[174,1231,807,829]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">1а. Pear-shaped proboscis with extension in the middle part. ........................................................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE519783E473C6C9EACFCD1F692FCB5" blockId="13.[174,1233,807,1463]" box="[174,1232,836,858]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<keyLead id="30ABBA4D3E473C6C9EACFCD1F692FCB5" box="[174,1232,836,858]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">1b. Proboscis other form...........................................................................................................................................3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30AE01DD3E473C6C9EACFCF4F692FC22" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<paragraph id="8BE519783E473C6C9EACFCF4F692FC7B" blockId="13.[174,1233,807,1463]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<keyLead id="30ABBA4D3E473C6C9EACFCF4F692FC7B" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
2a. In anterior and posterior parts of proboscis same 30–36 longitudinal hook rows. To a level of attachment of the proboscis receptacle 12–13 hooks in row. ................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A62FB3E473C6C9A64FCEBF692FC7B" authorityName="Van Cleave" authorityYear="1916" box="[1126,1232,894,916]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Centrorhynchidae" genus="Centrorhynchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="13" pageNumber="208" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="species" species="spinosus">
<emphasis id="B92EC56A3E473C6C9A64FCEBF692FC7B" box="[1126,1232,894,916]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">C. spinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE519783E473C6C9EACFC0FF692FC22" blockId="13.[174,1233,807,1463]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<keyLead id="30ABBA4D3E473C6C9EACFC0FF692FC22" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
2b. In anterior part of proboscis 34 longitudinal hook rows, in posterior part — 40. To a level of attachment of proboscis receptacle 9–10 hooks. ................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A62FB3E473C6C9A65FC22F692FC22" authorityName="Florescu" authorityYear="1940" box="[1127,1232,951,973]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Centrorhynchidae" genus="Centrorhynchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="13" pageNumber="208" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="species" species="narcisae">
<emphasis id="B92EC56A3E473C6C9A65FC22F692FC22" box="[1127,1232,951,973]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">C. narcisae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30AE01DD3E473C6C9EACFC41F692FBAF" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<paragraph id="8BE519783E473C6C9EACFC41F692FBE8" blockId="13.[174,1233,807,1463]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<keyLead id="30ABBA4D3E473C6C9EACFC41F692FBE8" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">3a. Anterior part of proboscis almost cylindrical without evident narrowing in level of attachment of proboscis receptacle..................................................................................................................................................4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE519783E473C6C9EACFB98F692FBAF" blockId="13.[174,1233,807,1463]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<keyLead id="30ABBA4D3E473C6C9EACFB98F692FBAF" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">3b. Anterior part of proboscis spherical or spade-shaped with evident narrowing in the level of attachment of proboscis receptacle........................................................................................................................................6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30AE01DD3E473C6C9EACFBD2F692FB95" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<paragraph id="8BE519783E473C6C9EACFBD2F692FBB2" blockId="13.[174,1233,807,1463]" box="[174,1232,1095,1117]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<keyLead id="30ABBA4D3E473C6C9EACFBD2F692FBB2" box="[174,1232,1095,1117]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
4а. Proboscis with 38–42 longitudinal hook rows of 26–27 hooks. ................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A62FB3E473C6C9A69FBD2F692FBB2" authorityName="Kukui" authorityYear="1929" box="[1131,1232,1095,1117]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Centrorhynchidae" genus="Centrorhynchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="13" pageNumber="208" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="species" species="magnus">
