<emphasis id="B92EC56A3E473C6C9A50FB14F692FB78" box="[1106,1232,1153,1175]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">C. amphibius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE519783E473C6C9EACFB08F692FB3F" blockId="13.[174,1233,807,1463]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<keyLead id="30ABBA4D3E473C6C9EACFB08F692FB3F" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
5b. Proboscis with 30–34 longitudinal hook rows. Blade of the largest hook 50–65 length. ............................ ..................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A62FB3E473C6C9A2CFB2FF692FB3F" authorityName="Luhe" authorityYear="1911" baseAuthorityName="Zeder" baseAuthorityYear="1800" box="[1070,1232,1210,1232]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Centrorhynchidae" genus="Centrorhynchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="13" pageNumber="208" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="species" species="globocaudatus">
<emphasis id="B92EC56A3E473C6C9A2CFB2FF692FB3F" box="[1070,1232,1210,1232]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">C. globocaudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30AE01DD3E473C6C9EACFB42F692FAE5" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<paragraph id="8BE519783E473C6C9EACFB42F693FB02" blockId="13.[174,1233,807,1463]" box="[174,1233,1239,1261]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<keyLead id="30ABBA4D3E473C6C9EACFB42F693FB02" box="[174,1233,1239,1261]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
6а. Each longitudinal row with 19–20 hooks. Eggs 45–55 × 25. ......................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A62FB3E473C6C9A14FB42F6D5FB02" authority="Lisitsyna &amp; Greben, 2015" authorityName="Lisitsyna &amp; Greben" authorityYear="2015" box="[1046,1175,1239,1261]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Centrorhynchidae" genus="Centrorhynchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="13" pageNumber="208" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="species" species="polissiensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B92EC56A3E473C6C9A14FB42F6D5FB02" box="[1046,1175,1239,1261]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">C. polissiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21D78113E473C6C9A9FFB42F693FB02" box="[1181,1233,1239,1261]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE519783E473C6C9EACFB61F692FAE5" blockId="13.[174,1233,807,1463]" box="[174,1232,1268,1290]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<keyLead id="30ABBA4D3E473C6C9EACFB61F692FAE5" box="[174,1232,1268,1290]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">6b. Each longitudinal row with 13–18 hooks. Eggs 56–72 × 28–35...................................................................7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30AE01DD3E473C6C9EACFA84F68FFAAC" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<paragraph id="8BE519783E473C6C9EACFA84F692FAC8" blockId="13.[174,1233,807,1463]" box="[174,1232,1297,1319]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<keyLead id="30ABBA4D3E473C6C9EACFA84F692FAC8" box="[174,1232,1297,1319]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
7а. First 7–10 hooks in each longitudinal row large with strong roots. ........................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A62FB3E473C6C9A64FA84F692FAC8" box="[1126,1232,1297,1319]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Polymorphidae" genus="Centrosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="13" pageNumber="208" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="species" species="buteonis">
<emphasis id="B92EC56A3E473C6C9A64FA84F692FAC8" box="[1126,1232,1297,1319]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">C. buteonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE519783E473C6C9EACFAB8F68FFAAC" blockId="13.[174,1233,807,1463]" box="[174,1229,1325,1347]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<keyLead id="30ABBA4D3E473C6C9EACFAB8F68FFAAC" box="[174,1229,1325,1347]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">7b. First 3–6 hooks in each longitudinal row large with strong roots. .............................................................. 8</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30AE01DD3E473C6C9EACFADFF692FA59" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<paragraph id="8BE519783E473C6C9EACFADFF692FA92" blockId="13.[174,1233,807,1463]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<keyLead id="30ABBA4D3E473C6C9EACFADFF692FA92" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
8а. First 3–5 (usually 4) hooks in each longitudinal row large with strong roots. Eggs 56–65 × 28–30. ........ ................................................................................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A62FB3E473C6C9A65FAF2F692FA92" authorityName="Luhe" authorityYear="1911" baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1780" box="[1127,1232,1383,1405]" class="Palaeacanthocephala" family="Centrorhynchidae" genus="Centrorhynchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polymorphida" pageId="13" pageNumber="208" phylum="Acanthocephala" rank="species" species="aluconis">
<emphasis id="B92EC56A3E473C6C9A65FAF2F692FA92" box="[1127,1232,1383,1405]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">C. aluconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE519783E473C6C9EACFA11F692FA59" blockId="13.[174,1233,807,1463]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<keyLead id="30ABBA4D3E473C6C9EACFA11F692FA59" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
8b. First 4–6 (usually 5) hooks in each longitudinal row large with strong roots. Eggs 68–72 × 33–35. ........ ............................................................................................................................................................ 
